***************************************************************
libLAS -- A C++ library for reading and writing LAS LiDAR data 
***************************************************************

This library is available under the terms of the `BSD License`_ 
for reading and writing LAS `LIDAR`_ data. It was originally developed by 
`Martin Isenburg and Jonathan Shewchuk`_ of the  University of North Carolina. 
Continuing development by Mateusz Loskot and Howard Butler is supported by 
the `IGSB`_ of the Iowa DNR for use in its state-wide `LIDAR`_ project.

The library currently only reads/writes LAS 1.0 and 1.1 data.  LAS 2.0 support
is not scheduled to be developed in the near future.  The library provides 
both a C and a C++ API along with some utility applications for manipulating 
LAS files (they utilize the C API).  

Limitations
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

As of version 0.9.0, the following is not supported:

 - Variable length headers (will be complete by 1.0.0)
 - Spatial reference interpretation
 - txt2las (port to new library is not complete)
 - lasdiff (port to new library is not complete)

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

See INSTALL for notes how to install libLAS on unix-like platforms.  Windows 
installation should be a simple as copying the dll and library executables to 
a path in which you wish to run them from.

-------------------------
LAS Format Specifications
-------------------------

LAS Format standard documents in PDF format:

* `LAS 2.0 Format Standard`_ (2007-05-01) - *Proposed*
* `LAS 1.1 Format Standard`_ (2005-05-07)
* `LAS 1.0 Format Standard`_ (2003-05-09)

The LAS Format Standard is maintained by `ASPRS Standards Committee`_.

